The paper discusses user profiling and privacy concerns in online social networks, which are topics that are typically studied in the fields of social informatics (cs.SI) and social computing (cs.SOC). The paper also discusses measures to minimize privacy leaks due to social graph data mining, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and database systems (cs.DB). Finally, the paper discusses the use of algorithms to perform user profiling, which could also be relevant to the field of cybernetics (cs.CYBER).
